---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const phone = '01623 325 123';
const telHref = `tel:${phone.replace(/\s+/g, '')}`;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Tyre Emergency Ltd | Dean Spicer, REACT Licensed Mobile Tyre Fitter"
  description="Tyre Emergency Ltd is a sole-operator mobile tyre service run by Dean Spicer from Bilsthorpe, Nottinghamshire. REACT licensed, in the tyre trade since his teens, and doing every job himself."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1>The person who won&rsquo;t leave you stranded.</h1>
      <p class="page-hero-sub">Tyre Emergency Ltd is a sole-operator business run by Dean Spicer from Bilsthorpe, Nottinghamshire. Every call, every quote and every job is handled by Dean personally &mdash; so the person you speak to on the phone is the same one who&rsquo;ll turn up at your door.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-white">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">The Story</span>
      <h2>In the tyre trade since his teens</h2>
      <p>Dean has been in the tyre game since he was a teenager &mdash; starting on the shop floor at a national chain, working through independent garages, spending time in management and ending up back on the tools because that&rsquo;s the bit he enjoys most. Tyres are what he knows best and it&rsquo;s what he keeps coming back to.</p>
      <p>Tyre Emergency Ltd was set up in December 2023 to do it his way: an exact price on the phone before he goes anywhere, a realistic ETA he actually sticks to, and a phone answered round the clock by the same person who&rsquo;ll be turning up at your door. Because it&rsquo;s a one-man operation, you get the same experienced fitter whether you ring at noon or midnight. No rota, no agency cover, no &ldquo;we&rsquo;ll get someone out to you eventually&rdquo;.</p>
      <p>The work covers cars, vans, SUVs, caravans, motorhomes and trailers, and there are over 450 five-star reviews on the back of it &mdash; every one earned by turning up when promised, doing the job right and being straight about what it costs.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-light">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">REACT Licensing</span>
      <h2>What &ldquo;REACT licensed&rdquo; actually means</h2>
      <p>REACT licensing is about one specific thing: working safely at the roadside. It covers how to set up a vehicle and equipment on A-roads and motorways, how to use cones and beacons properly, how to assess a scene before starting work, and how to keep yourself and the customer safe with traffic passing at speed. It&rsquo;s not a tick-box course either &mdash; your van has to meet certain standards and you need real roadside experience before you&rsquo;re even eligible.</p>
      <p>The practical difference for you: when we turn up on the M1 hard shoulder or the verge of an A-road at 2am, nobody&rsquo;s improvising. We know exactly how to set up, what to do if conditions change, and when the right answer is to wait for a lane closure rather than work somewhere dangerous. That makes the job safer for you, for passing traffic and for us.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center">
        <span class="eyebrow">How It Works</span>
        <h2>What to expect when you call</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-3 values-grid">
        <article class="value-card">
          <h3>An exact price on the phone</h3>
          <p>You get an all-in quote before we go anywhere. No call-out fees, no per-mile charges, no VAT added at the end. What you&rsquo;re told is what you pay.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="value-card">
          <h3>An ETA that actually means something</h3>
          <p>We give you a realistic ETA based on where we actually are, not a best-case figure to keep you on the call. If something changes, we ring. If we can&rsquo;t reach you fast enough, we say so.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="value-card">
          <h3>The right tyre, fitted properly</h3>
          <p>Tyres matched to the vehicle &mdash; correct size, load rating and speed rating &mdash; balanced and torque-wrenched before we leave. Not just slapped on with an impact gun.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-light">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">The Philosophy</span>
      <h2>An emergency is a bad enough day already.</h2>
      <p>Most people who call us are stressed. They&rsquo;re late for work, late for the airport, sat with the kids in a cold car on an unlit lane. They don&rsquo;t want a sales pitch and they don&rsquo;t want the whole thing to drag on any longer than it has to.</p>
      <p>So the call is kept short. We need three things: where you are, what you&rsquo;re driving and what&rsquo;s happened. We give you the price and the ETA, and you decide. When we arrive, we get straight to work and get you moving. That&rsquo;s the whole service model &mdash; and it&rsquo;s what five hundred reviews consistently say back.</p>
      <div class="cta-row about-cta">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href={telHref}>Call {phone}</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding: 5rem 0 3rem;
    background-color: var(--color-bg-white);
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    background-image:
      radial-gradient(900px 500px at 80% 20%, rgba(255, 45, 45, 0.08), transparent 60%);
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    max-width: 22ch;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
  }

  .page-hero-sub {
    color: var(--color-text-muted-dark);
    max-width: 60ch;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .values-grid {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .value-card {
    padding: 1.75rem;
    background-color: var(--color-bg-light);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    height: 100%;
  }

  .value-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .value-card p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted-dark);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .about-cta {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    justify-content: flex-start;
  }
</style>
